The writings of Occam, as well as those of Scotus, con- tributed especially to raise Logic to the rank of a distinct science, independent of its applied uses⁰. But they approached it from opposite sides. The principles of Occam, developed by modern philosophy, would lead us to the Logic of Kant: those of Scotus, almost to the Logic of Hegel.
